<br>
The regulations require background checks, fingerprinting and licensing of all transport personnel which raises logistical, financial and legal issues for transporters and their subcontractors. Consequently, USPS found itheir subcontractors unable to comply - therefore USPS refused to transport the regulated material.<br>
<br>
Just yesterday the Department of Transportation issued an exemption to Aerotech (a top producer of hobby rocket motors), along with 12 other vendors, enabling them to ship materials via alternate means.<br>
<br>
News of the exemption, and access to exemption text itself, can be reached at <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.aerotech-rocketry.com">www.aerotech-rocketry.com</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
It was only when the Homeland Security bill was in Congress that the Safe Explosives Act was ammended to it, and &quot;rode&quot; with it. Given how much deliberation was done with the Safe Explsoives Act prior to that, it is doubtful that the SEA would have been passed on it's own.<br>
